<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><title>Settings - Booking Admin</title><%- include('partials/head') %></head>
<body>
<div class="app-shell">
  <%- include('partials/sidebar') %>
  <div class="main">
    <h2>Settings</h2>
    <% if (cleared) { %><div class="success-box" style="max-width:480px">Operational data cleared — bookings, notifications, timesheets, roster shifts, and requests are all empty. Staff accounts, tables, and the menu are untouched.</div><% } %>
    <div class="card" style="max-width:480px">
      <form method="POST" action="/settings">
        <div class="field">
          <label>Default booking duration (minutes)</label>
          <input type="number" name="slotDurationMinutes" min="15" step="15" value="<%= settings.slotDurationMinutes %>">
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Send reminder this many hours before booking</label>
          <input type="number" name="reminderHoursBefore" min="1" value="<%= settings.reminderHoursBefore %>">
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Opening hour (24h)</label>
          <input type="number" name="openHour" min="0" max="23" value="<%= settings.openHour %>">
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Closing hour (24h)</label>
          <input type="number" name="closeHour" min="0" max="23" value="<%= settings.closeHour %>">
        </div>
        <button class="btn" type="submit">Save settings</button>
      </form>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="max-width:480px">
      <h3 style="margin-top:0">Email setup</h3>
      <p class="muted">Email sending is configured via environment variables in your <code>.env</code> file (SMTP_HOST, SMTP_PORT, SMTP_USER, SMTP_PASS, SMTP_FROM, ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL). See README for a Gmail example.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="max-width:480px">
      <h3 style="margin-top:0">Google Calendar sync</h3>
      <% if (googleConfigured) { %>
        <p><span class="badge confirmed">Connected</span></p>
        <dl class="detail-grid">
          <div><dt>Calendar ID</dt><dd><%= googleCalendarId %></dd></div>
          <div><dt>Last synced</dt><dd><%= googleSyncStatus.lastSyncAt ? new Date(googleSyncStatus.lastSyncAt).toLocaleString() : 'Not yet' %></dd></div>
          <div><dt>External events pulled in</dt><dd><%= googleSyncStatus.externalEventCount %></dd></div>
        </dl>
        <p class="muted">Bookings created, edited, or cancelled in this app are automatically pushed to that calendar. Events added directly on Google Calendar show up on the app's Calendar page (synced every 10 minutes).</p>
        <form method="POST" action="/settings/google-sync-now">
          <button class="btn small secondary" type="submit">Sync now</button>
        </form>
      <% } else { %>
        <p><span class="badge cancelled">Not configured</span></p>
        <p class="muted">Set <code>GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY_PATH</code> and <code>GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID</code> in your <code>.env</code> file to enable two-way sync with Google Calendar. See README for the one-time Google Cloud Console setup steps.</p>
      <% } %>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="max-width:480px;border-left:3px solid var(--danger)">
      <h3 style="margin-top:0">Danger zone</h3>
      <p class="muted">These also appear as quick-access buttons at the bottom of the sidebar on every page. Both are irreversible.</p>

      <div style="margin-bottom:18px">
        <strong>Clear data</strong>
        <p class="muted" style="margin:4px 0 8px">Wipes all bookings, notification logs, clock-in history, roster shifts, and staff requests. Staff accounts, tables, and the menu are kept as-is.</p>
        <form method="POST" action="/settings/clear-data" onsubmit="return confirm('Clear all bookings, notifications, timesheets, roster shifts, and requests?\n\nStaff accounts, tables, and the menu are kept. This cannot be undone.')">
          <button class="btn danger" type="submit">Clear data</button>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Factory reset</strong>
        <p class="muted" style="margin:4px 0 8px">Wipes absolutely everything — every booking, every staff account, tables, the menu, all of it — back to the app's defaults, and creates one fresh admin account from the credentials in <code>.env</code> (<code>ADMIN_EMAIL</code> / <code>ADMIN_PASSWORD</code>). You'll be logged out immediately.</p>
        <form method="POST" action="/settings/factory-reset" onsubmit="return confirm('This deletes EVERY booking, staff account, table, and menu item, and logs you out.\n\nType OK to confirm you understand this cannot be undone.') &amp;&amp; confirm('Really factory reset? This is your last chance to cancel.')">
          <button class="btn danger" type="submit">Factory reset</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
